	'csv_import_description' => array(
		-1 => '1. It is necessary to use an MS Excel worksheet to import data. The data must be entered into the worksheet in the following order, i.e. the names of the columns from left to right must be: Personal Identification Code, Given Name, Surname, Form, Year, Structural Unit, Chair, Position. The file imported to add statuses must at minimum include the following data: Personal Identification Code, Given Name, Surname. The file imported to remove statuses may containonly personal identification codes. If the data is in a different order, it can berearranged it in the course of importing, but it is recommended to use the prescribed order. 
<br /><br />
2. Select the card type, for which you would like to import data. Note: The persons, whose data is imported together, must be applying for the same type of card! 
<br /><br />
3. Add the data file. While importing the data file, make sure that the imported MS Excel file is saved in CSV format.
<br /><br />
4. The list separator must match the list separator specified in your computer settings. You can check this by selecting: Start – Control panel – Regional and Language options – Customize – List separator. The separator used in importing must match the separator indicated in the “List separator” selection. E.g., if semicolon is indicated in the“List separator” selection, you must also select semicolon as the list separator when importing data. 
<br /><br />
5. If the imported file includes a headline or a title row, checkmark the title row box. If there is no title row in the imported file, do not checkmark the box. 
<br /><br />
6.Click the button “Import users”. 
<br /><br />
7. If the order of columns in the imported data file differs from the one described in article 1, it is possible to rearrange the order. After that, all the imported data are displayed together in one table, where it is possible to confirm the data by person or leave it unconfirmed. To leave the data unconfirmed, the checkmark in the box on the row with the data that you wish to leave unconfirmed must be removed. If a problem has occurred in the course of importing or there is an error in the data of one of the applicants, the system will display the corresponding information or error message in the Status column. 
<br /><br />
